name: Laurel M. Lee
tweet: Senator Gwen Margolis is a longtime elected official whose achievements in office have paved the way for many women! In 1990, she became the first female president of the @FLSenate! She was re-elected in 2002 & inducted into the Women’s Hall of Fame in 2009. #WHM #FloridaFirsts  https://t.co/jvMo2pdAUs

name: Laurel M. Lee
tweet: As the guardians of state records & filings, Secretaries of State have long prioritized cybersecurity. name: Laurel M. Lee
tweet: #OTD in 1892, Great Floridian James Van Fleet was born! He was born in New Jersey, but almost immediately moved to Bartow, Florida! He was an infantry officer in the @USArmy, an ROTC instructor, and the head football coach @UF. Learn more on @FLMemory:  https://t.co/LoKj63xNmz  https://t.co/gMK2wFFHQZ

name: Laurel M. Lee
tweet: In 1972, Rhea Grossman became the first female to serve as a Justice of the Florida Supreme Court (@FLCourts)! Grossman sat in for Justice James C. Adkins who was working on judicial reform. Learn about other #FloridaFirsts here:  https://t.co/AUaE5uwRFx  Photos: @FLMemory #WHM  https://t.co/7o7UzDAwKN
